37 families, and persons with disabilities; and the chairs of the joint committee on aging and
38 independence on the results of its investigation and its recommendations, including proposals of
39 legislation or regulations necessary to carry its recommendations into effect.
40 The commission shall dissolve 30 days after the submission of the report, unless upon a
41 two-thirds vote of the commission, a continuance is deemed necessary to complete the purpose
42 of the commission. The time frame of said continuance must be specified in the motion to extend
43 time of operation.
